legislating a rule for monetary policy siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display legislating a rule for monetary policy type siepr discussion paper 10 032 author s john taylor published 07 1 11 download pdf abstract i discuss a proposal to legislate a rule for monetary policy the proposal modernizes laws first passed in the late 1970s but largely discarded in 2000 it would thereby restore reporting and accountability requirements for the instruments of monetary policy it would limit but not eliminate discretion the proposal provides a degree of control by the political authorities without interfering in the day to day operations of monetary policy full text full text stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
